04792nam a22005415i 9780226298269DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20082007ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802262982697 a10.7208/97802262982692doi  a(DE-B1597)524350  a(OCoLC)1135590219  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aB832b.G53 2007 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04a320.08996073a973/.04960731 aGlaude, Eddie S., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aIn a Shade of Blue :bPragmatism and the Politics of Black America /cEddie S. Glaude. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2008] 4c©2007  a1 online resource (208 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAcknowledgments -- t1. In a Shade of Blue: An Introduction -- t2. “Black and Proud”: Reconstructing Black Identity -- t3. “Ethiopia Shall Stretch Forth Her Hands unto God”: The Problem of History in Black Theology -- t4. Agency, Slavery, and African American Christianity -- t5. Explicating Black Nationalism -- t6. The Eclipse of a Black Public and the Challenge of a Post-Soul Politics -- tEpilogue: The Covenant with Black America -- tNotes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn this provocative book, Eddie S. Glaude Jr., one of our nation’s rising young African American intellectuals, makes an impassioned plea for black America to address its social problems by recourse to experience and with an eye set on the promise and potential of the future, rather than the fixed ideas and categories of the past. Central to Glaude’s mission is a rehabilitation of philosopher John Dewey, whose ideas, he argues, can be fruitfully applied to a renewal of African American politics. According to Glaude, Dewey’s pragmatism, when attentive to the darker dimensions of life—or what we often speak of as the blues—can address many of the conceptual problems that plague contemporary African American discourse. How blacks think about themselves, how they imagine their own history, and how they conceive of their own actions can be rendered in ways that escape bad ways of thinking that assume a tendentious political unity among African Americans simply because they are black. Drawing deeply on black religious thought and literature, In a Shade of Blue seeks to dislodge such crude and simplistic thinking and replace it with a deeper understanding of and appreciation for black life in all its variety and intricacy. Glaude argues that only when black political leaders acknowledge such complexity can the real-life sufferings of many African Americans be remedied, an argument echoed in the recent rhetoric and optimism of the Barack Obama presidential campaign. In a Shade of Blue is a remarkable work of political commentary and to follow its trajectory is to learn how African Americans arrived at this critical moment in their cultural and political history and to envision where they might head in the twenty-first century. “Eddie Glaude is the towering public intellectual of his generation.”—Cornel West “Eddie Glaude is poised to become the leading intellectual voice of our generation, raising questions that make us reexamine the assumptions we hold by expanding our inventory of ideas.”—Tavis Smiley  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and government. 0aAfrican AmericansxReligion. 0aPragmatism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226298269423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226298269.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles